"To solve the system of equations given by:\n1. \\( 725x + 727y = 1500 \\)\n2. \\( 729x + 731y = 1508 \\)\n\nWe first use the method of elimination to find the values of \\( x \\) and \\( y \\). By subtracting the first equation from the second, we simplify the system to:\n\\[ 4x + 4y = 8 \\]\n\nDividing the entire equation by 4, we get:\n\\[ x + y = 2 \\]\n\nNow, substituting \\( y = 2 - x \\) into the first equation:\n\\[ 725x + 727(2 - x) = 1500 \\]\nwhich simplifies to:\n\\[ -2x + 1454 = 1500 \\]\n\\[ -2x = 46 \\]\n\\[ x = -23 \\]\n\nSubstituting \\( x = -23 \\) back into \\( x + y = 2 \\):\n\\[ -23 + y = 2 \\]\n\\[ y = 25 \\]\n\nFinally, calculating \\( x - y \\):\n\\[ x - y = -23 - 25 = -48 \\]\n\nThus, the values are \\( x = -23 \\), \\( y = 25 \\), and \\( x - y = -48 \\).\n```"